- "stars that have shone" refers to players who have played in the game;
- "for more than 20 minutes" refers to the condition where the player's minutes played (min) is greater than 20;
- "average score" refers to the average fantasy points.

- A team's "home team score" refers to the points scored by the team when they are the home team in a game;
- The "average home team score" is the mean score of all home teams across all games;
- "Total home points" is the sum of all points scored by a team when they were the home team.

- "high average fantasy points per minute" refers to players who have a significant contribution in terms of fantasy points relative to their play time;
- "played in at least 10 games" ensures that the player has enough data points to be considered consistent;
- "typically play more than 10 minutes per game" ensures that the player has a substantial role in the games they play.

- A "shining star" in basketball refers to a player who excels in multiple aspects of the game, such as scoring, rebounding, and assisting;
- "Guards" are typically responsible for ball handling, scoring, and setting up plays;
- "Points" (pts) refer to the number of points a player scores in a game;
- "Rebounds" (reb) refer to the number of times a player retrieves the ball after a missed shot;
- "Assists" (ast) refer to the number of times a player passes the ball to a teammate who then scores.

- "elite quintet" refers to the top 5 teams;
- "stand tallest in the league with the heaviest wallets" refers to the teams with the highest average salary per player;
- "reveal their average height and weight" refers to the average physical attributes of the players on those teams.

- 'Shining stars' refers to the top-performing teams;
- 'Leading the pack' means having the highest total points scored;
- 'Each season' refers to different years or periods in which the games were played.

- A "winning team" is a team that has more wins than losses in the games they have played;
- "Cumulative average points" refers to the sum of a player's average points over all games, as they contribute to their team's overall performance;
- "Rise through the ranks" means being listed in order of their average points, with the highest scorers at the top.

- 'stands out as the one with the tallest players on average' refers to the team with the highest average height;
- 'the team that not only boasts the tallest players but also the one where the players are the heaviest and earn the most' refers to the team with the highest average values for height, weight, and salary;
- 'tops the charts in player earnings' refers to the team with the highest average salary.

- Fantasy points are a numerical representation of a player's performance in a fantasy sports league;
- "Consistently shone" refers to players who have played multiple games and maintained a high average of fantasy points;
- "Brightest stars leading the way" implies the players with the highest average fantasy points are listed first.
